channel.title: Help! WebClient Connection error, wont extract cache
channel.description:
Hey again,
After recently finding a tutorial on how to make a WebClient, (ric914's webclient tutorial), and following it to the letter I discovered whenever my WebClient loads, it says downloading cache, gets to 100%, says unpacking files.. and then says 'Client Updated - Please Reload' and then it says 'Connection error retrying in 10 9 8 etc'
Could somebody please help me as what could be the problem that is causing this?
Also after this happens i check the directory that i specify in the signlink.java and the cache hasnt been extracted...
Help me please!

item.dc:creator: @baby_kid13 baby_kid13
item.description:
@baby_kid13 wrote:

Webclients are very easy following ric’s tut but you gotta know how to work out errors and if you ever coded client/servers then you should be able to work it out and i can tell you your problem i had the same problem what it is doing is either reading more than one file and putting it in the cache folder or you dont have the link rite in client.java or you named it cache but in client.java put it as something else or your signlink.java is specified as something but in your sprites there not specified to read from the same spot but if you cant figure out the problem i wouldnt mind helping you or even doing it for you
